ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: ERS 900 offers ERS graduate students a communal space for dialogue and research. Although it was a vital part of my first semester in college I'm not sure that non-ERS students would benefit from the class in the same way that ERS students do.
Take it - the discussions are enlightening (and enlivening)

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: I gained a great deal of practical knowledge about the publication process, job market, and life in academia on top of a strong grounding in European Studies.
It didn't,though I wish it did.

The course enhanced my knowledge of the academic profession and of academic publishing especially. It also contributed to my eventual thesis by allowing me to briefly explore a new methodology without fear of backfiring.
